baseName.value: Monobloc tanks in reinforced precast concrete for water treatment

generalComment.value:
The primary data collected in this study refers to production for the year 2022.



Based on M3


No cut-off elements were considered, therefore it is believed that the data represents at least 99% of the total flows (mass and energy) of phases A1, A2 and A3.

technologicalApplicability.value:
"Water treatment tanks are systems use in order to recycle and to collection industrial, rain or meteoric water or to reuse pre-assembled systems. They can be used, based on the relative type (monobloc), also in systems firefighting, in water purification, in the field of liquid storage, in first rain systems, in oil separators, etc.
They are produced in reinforced concrete, with a designed structure to ensure safety against damage and towards the people, hydraulic seal and maximum versatility during inspection, maintenance, etc."

 This EPD examines the calculated average product performance of the following products:
Circular tank of Lt. 3,500 "TACS3500" and circular driveway slab "TAC3500/20"
Circular tank of Lt. 6,800 "TACS6800" and circular driveway slab "TAC6800/20"
9,800 litre circular tank "TACS/9800" and circular driveway slab "TAC9800/20"
Rectangular 12,500 litre tank "TACS12500" and walkable slab "TASQ250/13" or driveable slab "TASQ250/20"
Rectangular tank of Lt. 25,700 "TACS25700" and walkable slab "TASR504250/13" or driveable "TASR504250/20"
Rectangular tank of Lt. 38,900 "TACS38900" and walkable slab "TASR750250/13" or driveable "TASR750250/20"
Rectangular tank of Lt. 52,100 "TACS52100" and walkable slab "TASR1000250/13" or driveable "TASR1000250/20"
